radiographic_examinations.findings: Imaged lung bases are clear. The liver, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands appear normal. Kidneys show no signs of hydronephrosis or stones. No signs of free air or free fluid in the abdomen. There is a calcified structure within the mid body of the appendix compatible with appendicolith, with a dilated appendix and significant periappendiceal fat stranding, indicating acute appendicitis. No free fluid or lymphadenopathy in the deep pelvis.
